Terraform taint
How to limit the resource usage in K8s

Ans. First, I always define CPU and memory requests and limits for every container

Second, at the namespace level, I use LimitRanges to enforce default, minimum, 
and maximum values so teams can’t deploy pods without proper sizing.

Horizontal Pod Autoscaling, which scales replicas based on CPU, memory, or custom metrics. 
This keeps individual pods from being overloaded while maintaining performance

I use Vertical Pod Autoscaler to recommend or automatically adjust resource requests based on actual usage.


Asked me to write request and limit usage YAML file
Ans.
apiVersion: v1
kind: ResourceQuota
metadata:
  name: dev-quota
  namespace: dev
spec:
  hard:
    requests.cpu: "10"
    requests.memory: 20Gi
    limits.cpu: "20"
    limits.memory: 40Gi
    pods: "50"

